caption.text:
Let me give you some advice ⬇️

Content Doesn’t Need to complicated to create! I LOVE helping and guiding you guys along the way, try using this audio which is currently trending and the vocal is a great way to give advice, challenge a belief or bust a myth people might have about your niche.

Let me give you some advice….

I’ve given a couple of examples below of text you could use, but always make sure your hook points at your business as the answer to the claim you’re making
Examples:

“Let me give you some advice, fasted cardio is not the best way to cut fat….a balanced programme that takes into account your goals and diet will help you reach and maintain your target weight quicker - personal trainer

“Let me give you some advice, washing your jewellery in a diluted solution of dish soap and warm water with bring back sparkle to any precious stones “ - handmade jewellery

Let’s hear your caption below? 8’ happy to help tweak!

The course I’m writing is going to be jam packed with content prompts and ideas for you to use on your own Instagram page, comment REGISTER now to join the waitlist and be first to hear when it launches

#iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy

caption.text:
Share if you relate🫶🏻

If you have a friend or a family member in business, even if that business isn’t the best fit for you personally, show them some love. 

It’s free to be a supporter and as a small business owner, it makes ALL the difference 

I have a platform here, Introduce yourself and your business below, and perhaps you’ll find of “your people” in the comments section ⬇️

#smallbusinesssupport #smallbusinesslife #instagramgrowthexpert #iggrowth #embracesocials

Let’s talk about the ugly truth of owning a small business that isn’t often highlighted. 

The reality is that success isn’t always steady. One week, your instagram account might be booming with engagement, inbox full of enquiries, and bottom line soaring with sales ££, but the next, it can feel like crickets 🥹

Your profits can fluctuate just as wildly as your reach — thousands of people one week and dropping to nothing the next. 

The emotional highs and crushing lows are intense, and the pressure to consistently perform can be overwhelming. This is the unglamorous side of the business journey that many don’t share, but it’s a struggle every entrepreneur faces 

I see you, I know the difference a like, a share and a nice comment can make.

caption.text:
Share Reviews ⬇️

Reviews are one of the post powerful ways to share wins and build trust with your audience! They something I try and do regularly to help me con each with my audience!

Try this tutorial for a fun way to share a review to your instagram account! The filter can be used over and over with different images in the background, and different reviews on screen!

You’ll want to save this reel so you don’t forget the steps!

- tap and begin a new story, tap camera, create, and slide across to gif

- type into the search bar “Crtm” and this loads a selection of screens, I chose the first option.

- now go you your sticker tab, type review and choose your favourite sticker to place on screen. 

- now go you your photo album and copy the text from a client review you previously screenshot and paste the review on screen. Use the colour picker to use a colour to compliment the post, and resize until the text fits nicely within the allocated space.

- lastly, if you want to add some personality, go to your photo album, and add any photo of you or your product.

If you love this instagram story idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

But remember if you want some more detailed help on how to grow your Instagram audience, comment GUIDE below and I’ll send over a link to the strategy I wrote myself which has gained me almost 350,000 followers this year 🚀

Instagram tips growth strategy marketing coach manager how to grow on Instagram hacks viral small business owner digital products online social media mentor passive income guide

#instagramforbusiness #instagramgrowth #instagramtips

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram Secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
This is a touchy subject..

I coach small business owners every day of the week, and I have to say this is a topic that comes up regularly but it’s not one I hear people speak about much.

First of all, more people buy followers than you think, I totally understand why, when credibility is often linked with popularity it can seem like the easy thing to do- but, I’m often surprised by the brand or businesses that succumb to this only wanting the best for their business , and it can be hugely damaging to your account. 

If you ask me if it’s ever a good idea, I will always say no, especially in 2024 Instagram has technologies so advanced you would risk losing your whole account together. 

So, why shouldn’t you buy followers?
Let me break it down:

When you have strategic and organic growth, you are planning for a certain kind of following and their situations or needs

Buying followers means any random person or bot with any background could end up on your page all of your hard work will then be seen by these likely bot or uninterested followers and not your real ones
Your genuine engagement will plummet and in the eyes of the algorithm you are no longer creating “interesting content” so the account essentially fizzles out.

Instagram relies on an active and interested audience and buying followers destroys pages daily, personally I could never risk it!

The process of trying to remove fake followers and get traction in your account is a complicated, lengthy and not always successful one.

Trust me, NEVER buy followers!! Just follow me! I’ll keep you updated with all instagram news and tips as it happens! 

I’d love to hear your thoughts, 
have you ever done it? 
Do you know people that have? 
Have you ever been asked or approached 

Lemme know and chat below
#instagramgrowthhacks #smallnusinesslife #iggrowth #contentcreatoruk

caption.text:
I will never apologise 

I’m never going to be sorry for talking to this incredible community I have built on Instagram EVERY SINGLE DAY 

There are now over 340,000 of you here learning about Instagram Growth and it almost didn’t happen, the first instagram coaching page I created last year was disabled due to an identity error, I was devastated when it happened and almost threw the towel in on the whole thing. I was so frustrated.

Imagine if I had quit then…imagine if I had let that frustration get the better of me and I just stopped posting because I wasn’t getting the result I wanted…

Instead I started over and focused on

1. Who I can help with my knowledge
2. I create simple content to help them move towards their goal 
3. I show up every day to increase trust and move audiences through the customer journey with me

You should never feel bad for talking about what you do, who you can help and what you love to create!

I am almost finished my full Instagram Growth Course, it’s going to take you by the hand and walk you through the whole niche, marketing, research, messaging, posting, hooks, shooting, reviewing and refining process, if you want to be the first to hear when I launch later this month, and grab a discount too, then reply to this post REGISTER and join the waitlist! I can’t wait to share 

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy #smallbusinesslife #smallbusinessowner #smallbusinessuk 

Do you post about your business every day?

text_info_list.text: sharing my own strategy that actually teaches you how to grow on Instagram?
that has gained me over 340,000 followers this year

caption.text:
Easy Trick to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new audiences, but stories are the best way to connect current followers….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

 - Tap and begin a new story, add a photo you want to act as the background for your reel you are sharing. 

- go to the text tab, with white background on, do a full stop and 6 spaces, and places that box on the left hand side of the screen. This box will act as a frame for you.

- add some further text give some information and context about the reel you are sharing. Now save this as an image.

- Go to the reel, you would like to share, tap the aeroplane and share to story.

- Resize the reel in the left of the screen of the screen, hold down and slide down to bring the reel forwards, and place it on the white box background you created.

- Go to your stickers tab, type “new reel black” and choose the sticker to place on top of the reel

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

I’m always here to help you with your content, comment EMBRACE and I’ll send you a weeks worth of reels prompts you can use this week.

caption.text:
So you probably want to know why…

As somebody who has coached hundreds of business and grown millions of followers on Instagram, I never hate keep what I have learned:

If I’m prioritising growth, here’s why I would never post 

1. Personal Posts

A new follower doesn’t know you, or feel anything for you yet, so although your personal updates are important to you, they probably arnt to them (yet)  Instead, when focusing on growth, think about your viewer, and make content for them, about them and show how you can serve them!

2. Long Reels

One of the metrics the algorithm looks at when figuring out what content to promote is watch time. A new audience who doesn’t know who you are or what you’re about may not stick around for a long video. So, 
Focus on “hooking” the viewer the first few seconds of your Reels with your text or visual hooks and be sure to add actionable steps, advice or value.

3. Adverts
Audiences hate feeling like they’re being sold to, so instead to simply “selling” and asking for customer’s for the thing you do, talk about the benefits your business offers. If you are making a direct sales post, use your story where you can give a clickable link & context. 

I’ve got a 50 page growth guide that can help you with this even more! Hundreds of others grabbed it to simplify their Instagram growth journey! You next?

Comment GUIDE and I’ll whiz a link right over 🫶🏻

#instagramgrowthstrategy #instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy #instagramgrowthhacks

text_info_list.text:
3 things I would never
post if I wanted to GROW on Instagram

caption.text:
I wish everyone knew…

Creating content for Instagram doesn’t need to be hard work.

If you incorporate and shoot snippets of what you are doing in your daily life into your content you will never run out of content ideas, for as long as you’re living and existing your story continues, so your content can continue.

I use small clips of my life and my business journey to help me market and promote my businesses! 

Shoot a short 5-7 second video and Add this hook, to break a common myth pr give us a fact in your industry. Examples ⬇️

I wish everyone knew that…

I wish everyone knew that you can lose belly fat and eat chocolate if you just…

I wish everyone knew that 2 breaths in through the nose and 1 out the mouth will calm your anxiety 

I everyone knew that buying a handmade gift is showing your love is a handmade way

Comment your niche below, and maybe we can all suggest some myths to bust, or facts to deliver, remembering to be purposeful and simple with what you could post about!

#reelsideas #reelstips #instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #contentstrategy #backtoschool #smallbusinessowner #smallbusinessuk

caption.text:
This got me 2.8M views!

The first time I created this viral style story effect it got me 2.8M views! This story idea is a great way to give a sneak peek into a project you are working on or a glimpse into your life!

It’s so simple to do you’ll wonder how you haven’t tried it before!

First off, don’t forget to save this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- tap and begin a new reel loading any image you would like to showcase, could be product or service image. Go to your sparkles tab, and search for the filter “ZoomblurT” and apply it. This turns your image into a blurred to clear video. Now save this video and close the screen.

- tap and begin a new story and add the blur to clear video you just made.

- Now go to your draw tool, Got to the colour picker tool, select any colour in the photo, choose the highlighter pen, hold down to colour the whole screen

- now go to your text tab, and type a letter O, resize the O to fill the screen.

- now go back to your pen tool,  choose the eraser brush on large and erase the colour from inside the letter O.

- Go to sticker tab again, type link, and add a link to your business or brand, and then any custom sticker text if you like,

- Now go to your sticker tab again, and choose a sticker to place over your link, can be any text to suit theme of your post.

This is such a simple effect you could use over and over again with different video and text! Let me know if this tutorial helped!

I share new ideas daily to help inspire your instagram content and help you grow and learn your way around instagram! 🚀❤️

Now you have an idea for your post design, make sure you’re following daily as I post new tips every day to help you on your instagram journey.

If you comment REGISTER below, you can be the first to hear about my Instagram growth course I’m launching which is packed full of video lessons, worksheets, prompts and tips to help you master Instagram without the guesswork! 

#socialmediahelp #socialmediamarketing #socialmediagrowth #instagramgrowthtips #reelsideas #reelsinspo #storyidea

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
If you are trying to grow your profile on Instagram, you’re in the right place. ♥️

I don’t gate keep here, and I do my level best to explain Instagram in language you can understand with simple steps you can follow.  Comment the word GUIDE below, to get a link to the strategy I wrote and followed to grow over 300,000 followers on Instagram this year!

Here’s what my students say 

I started implementing your strategy. It’s mad how many people I am now reaching with each post compared to 1 month ago x

l’ve just finished reading your guide and wanted to say thank you so much... this is a brilliant step by step guideline on how Instagram works and I finally understand it!!

I never thought it was possible, but I saw your growth and you make it look so easy. Now I’m using the guide I have 10k, and for a small business. That is massive!

#instagramgrowthstrategy #instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #contentmarketing

caption.text:
1 photo reel ⬇️

This is one of the most SIMPLE instagram reels you will ever create, you only need one photo and instagram will do the rest! ⬇️
I’m all about working smarter, not harder.

You can theme this anyway you’d like by choosing your own text and image!! Just don’t forget to SAVE so you don’t forget!

Here is the step by step guide below:

- go to start a new reel

- Upload any image of your choice 

- Now go to the sparkles filters button and tap the magnifying glass

- Type “Polaroid by f” and select the same filter as me

- This is now a reel, move you video to right leaving border on left.

- go to stickers tab and type in moving line, use the same sticker as me and place it over the line where the reel meets the border space.

- Now just choose your favourite font, and place the text in the space on the left-hand side.

Don’t forget a useful caption Add a catchy hook, if you are struggling to come up with one, comment HOOK below and I’ll send my free guide, plus 100 captions for you try 🎁

Be sure to SAVE this post so you don’t forget and let me know if you use this trick!!

#socialmediahelp #socialmediamarketing #socialmediagrowth #instagramgrowthtips #reelsideas #reelsinspo #storyidea

clips_metadata.reusable_text_attribute_string: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know…

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
Share if you feel it too…

Calling all the multitasking mums, persevering pet parents, and determined dads out there, if you have kept that business going, kept everyone fed and watered all summer long- then I’d call that a business win….

Just know I am SO close to having something super special ready for you, it’s going to take away the guess work, and give you the tools and the skills you need to make Instagram feel like fun again! So you can enjoy creating content for your business, and spend the rest of your time with whoever you love the most.

Comment REGISTER below, and join the waitlist to be the first to hear when I launch and grab early bird pricing at the same time!

Don’t forget to share with someone who can relate 

#instagramgrowthstrategy #smallbusinesslife #smallbusinesssupport #smallbusinessowner #iggrowth #instagramgrowth #contentcreator
